comments.body:
@iSazonov I mean within secretmanagement's core there could theoretically be a Set-Secret -AsUser option that would impersonate to the user/gmsa/msa context, but honestly you could just psexec a powershell session and then run set-secret to do the same thing (this is what I typically do when configuring secretmanagement for service accounts)

Secretmanagement uses a registry manifest in the user profile directly to direct to registered vaults, so if the user/service account doesn't have a profile, secretmanagement won't work.

I'd defer to @PaulHigin whether it's something he may want to put on the secretmanagement 2.0 roadmap. Agreed it's a very common scenario to want to configure a secret management vault for a service account or other noninteractive "runas" account so that it can retrieve required secrets, and currently the process is somewhat arduous at best and impossible at worst.
